Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveAs the scramble for the APC presidential ticket becomes more frantic, the battle in the southwest may end up becoming a two-man affair: APC national leader Bola Tinubu and his politically orphaned godson and V.P. Yemi Osinbajo.

Tinubu’s foot soldiers began their march earlier, unlike Osinbajo’s who were not sure of where their champ would swing—until last Monday.
Tinubu’s army of youth organized their first rally in Lagos on Saturday.
